    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty grim assessment lol. i mean, you say \"many analysts\" call it a failure, but some people argue that the alternative—letting Gaddafi just massacre everyone in Benghazi—would have been a much worse geopolitical disaster for US moral standing and regional stability. wouldn't you say that preventing a genocide is a massive strategic win regardless of the messy aftermath?",
